Please enter your username.Ill be Nighthale! Aiden decided at once.Once everything was set, a flash of white light surrounded him.Very quickly, Aiden materialized inside the game.Without even glancing at his surroundings, he immediately opened his Attributes Panel and looked nervously toward the bottom-right corner.Sure enough, there it was—a golden button with the word Reload.Aiden exhaled in relief.Thankfully, the games mechanics hadnt changed since his rebirth.This meant it was time for the best part.Chapter 3 Aidens Secondary Hidden Class, the WealthmancerAidens heart raced as his hands trembled.He reached for the golden button on the screen and slammed on it.Please enter the amount you wish to top up.He didnt even hesitate before maxing it out entirely.Aiden kept his life savings in his bank account, including the two billion he made from selling his shares, plus another 50 million hed borrowed by mortgaging his luxury villa.Together with what hed saved before, he had a total of 2.2 billion.Each dollar equaled one mark, which meant he would receive 2.2 billion marks in the game.If anyone ever found out hed dumped that kind of money into a game, theyd probably call him insane.To Aiden, it was a deal straight from heaven.Three days from now, the value of these marks would skyrocket once Doomsday was officially launched and synced with reality.One mark would equal 10 dollars.Once the reload was successful, his 2.2 billion marks would be worth 22 billion dollars—ten times what hed started with.And even that number couldnt capture their real value.The reload system would only be available for ten minutes during the private beta launch.Nearly no one would think of topping up, and those who did would only spend small amounts.Upon the games official release, in-game currency would become scarce.Sure, players could still buy marks with cash, but it would be difficult to convert huge sums like ten billion.As time went on, players would realize just how critical marks were.They might sell off small amounts to cover real-life expenses, but no one would be dumb enough to sell everything.There would be demand without supply.Meanwhile, Aidens 2.2 billion marks would be his startup capital for the new world.As Aiden keyed in the figure, his pulse quickened.Realistically, a financial transfer this massive would have triggered multiple alerts from government regulators.No game would ever allow such a transaction to go through instantly.However, Doomsday wasnt just any ordinary game.Even so, he couldnt help but feel uneasy, wondering if itd work this time.Congratulations, your top-up is successful!Yeah!Moments later, Aiden clenched his fists in excitement as a line of astronomical numbers appeared on the screen.He remembered an old saying that money couldnt buy happiness, but it could make a persons entire week.Right now, Aiden was experiencing that high.With this kind of starting advantage, plus everything he remembered about Doomsday, he was confident that he could rise to the very top.Hed even crush those nepo babies who had every resource at their fingertips.Ding!Suddenly, a crisp mechanical chime sounded.Congratulations, Nighthale. You are the first player to reload your system, with a single recharge exceeding one billion marks. A rare hidden class reward has been unlocked.Ding!Hidden class detected. Updating the system…Ding!You have obtained a secondary class—the Wealthmancer. Your current classes include Beastmaster and the Wealthmancer.What? You can unlock hidden classes just by spending money? Aiden froze for a second, then burst out laughing in disbelief and delight.Beyond the typical classes players could start with or evolve into, rare hidden classes existed as well.These could only be unlocked by meeting very specific, mysterious conditions.There was an unspoken rule that hidden classes werent necessarily the strongest, but the strongest always came from a hidden class.Their attributes and talents were far beyond anything ordinary classes could offer.That was why even a rumor about a hidden class was enough to send the entire player base into a frenzy.Meanwhile, what Aiden received wasnt just a hidden class—it was a secondary class.This meant his original starting class hadnt been replaced at all.He was now both a Beastmaster and the Wealthmancer.Aiden quickly pulled up his Attributes Panel to check on his Wealthmancers stats.You are now viewing attributes for the Wealthmancer.Innate Talent: Fortune Flux (Level 1). As a Wealthmancer, you possess the ability to generate wealth. Your total marks increase by one percent each day.Innate Talent: Vaultbound (Level 1). A Wealthmancer never loses whats his. Upon death, you retain all marks and items.Innate Talent: Divine Prosperity (Level 1). Wealth attracts fortune. Permanently increases Luck by 50 points.Innate Talent: Absolute Aura (Level 1). Even the shabbiest man shines when hes generous. Permanently increases Charisma by 50 points.Innate Talent: Power of Wealth (Level 1). A Wealthmancer remains a divine being. For every one million marks you spend, gain one random attribute point. Maximum of 100 points per day.Gosh! Aiden froze in shock, his eyes widening.He knew a hidden class like the Wealthmancer would come in handy, but not this powerful!Any one of these talents alone could shake the entire game, but having all five?This shook Aiden to the core, even when he had already experienced the game in his past life.He rubbed his eyes again just to make sure he wasnt hallucinating.Forget the rest.For starters, Fortune Flux was already an amazing talent.With 2.2 billion in his possession, that talent meant an extra 22 million marks every single day without having to do anything!Paired with the Power of Wealth, Aiden could splurge on anything, only to have his attributes grow even stronger.Just spending for fun would earn him 22 attribute points per day, which was insane.The more I spend, the more powerful I become. Now thats awesome!Vaultbound was another useful talent.After all, death penalties were brutal beyond belief in Doomsday.If a player got killed, theyd lose 20 percent of all their attributes.Worse, every piece of gear, item, and mark they carried would drop on the spot.Because of that, most players never carried much and kept their marks in the NPC-run banks instead.But unlike actual banks, the ones in Doomsday did not pay interest.On the contrary, these banks charged players outrageous storage fees instead.The more one deposited, the higher the fee.For instance, if Aiden stored all his 2.2 billion marks in a bank, hed have to pay 22 million marks every three months just for safekeeping.Aiden would lose 88 million a year just to keep his money in a vault.To make things worse, there was always the risk of a bank owner disappearing with everyones savings.The rules were unfair, but players had to abide by them.For years, storing marks had been one of the biggest challenges in Doomsday.Now that Aiden had obtained Vaultbound, he didnt have to worry about that anymore.He could keep his marks with him, enjoy as Fortune Flux grew his wealth, and never lose anything if he died.A glint flashed across Aidens eyes as he smirked.Once I make a name for myself, I could open my own private bank. Ill charge a lower storage fee…Ill earn interest off my clients marks, and grow that with Fortune Flux. Its a guaranteed profit with no risk at all!Hed use other peoples money to make himself richer, and theyd even thank him for it afterward.Now that was what being a Wealthmancer was all about.

Stop wasting your time on Langley. Shes not worth it.He added, Youre a Kroger, for Gods sake. Dont act like some lovesick idiot and embarrass the family.Aiden couldnt help but chuckle to himself, finding the whole thing absurd.Even his lifelong rival, who had always coveted his shares, could see Piper for the shallow, manipulative woman she was.So why hadnt he seen it himself before?As for Carters parting words, Aiden paid them no attention.He looked at the long string of zeros in his account balance and smiled.When Doomsday arrived, theyd see soon enough who truly stood above the rest.…Welcome to Doomsday, private beta launch.Congratulations, Aiden. Youve been selected to participate. This testing phase will last for three days, and the public beta launch will be available then.Please select your starting class, Aiden.It was Sunday, just like in his previous life, when Aiden clicked on that mysterious link that led him to the private beta launch of Doomsday.He could choose any of the starting classes—Warrior, Knight, Sorcerer, or even Farmer.In his past life, Aiden had chosen Knight.Back then, hed naively thought himself a knight who vowed to guard his princess forever.Looking back now, it was beyond stupid.Aiden almost gagged at the thought, feeling the same secondhand embarrassment as when adults found their old, cringey Snapchat stories.A knight guarding his princess? Please, thats just another name for a doormat.And Piper? A princess? Pfft!If anything, shed only become one because hed built her the castle himself.And now, the only place he wanted to escort her to was hell.Enough with that dumb crap. Whoever wants to be a knight, be my guest. Ill be a Beastmaster instead!He cursed under his breath and chose Beastmaster without hesitation.Aiden had thought it through carefully, and it hadnt been out of spite.In Doomsday, Beastmasters were widely recognized as the class with the highest potential.In his previous life, Aiden had heard of a legendary incident.An elite guild in Grendola once offended a god-tier Beastmaster, simply because they thought they had the numbers and manpower.The Beastmaster lost his temper and summoned his divine beast, the Netherwyrm.Together, the man and his dragon wiped the entire guild off the map.The guildmaster got killed multiple times until his attributes dwindled immensely, and he ended up dying in real life too.No other class could match that kind of destructive power.Of course, the strength of a Beastmaster came at a cost.Training beasts required an absurd amount of resources, way beyond what any normal player could afford.Owning a divine beast like the Netherwyrm required an infinite amount of resources.However, Aiden couldnt care less, for money was the least of his problems.You have completed your selection. Please enter your username.Ill be Nighthale! Aiden decided at once.Once everything was set, a flash of white light surrounded him.Very quickly, Aiden materialized inside the game.Without even glancing at his surroundings, he immediately opened his Attributes Panel and looked nervously toward the bottom-right corner.Sure enough, there it was—a golden button with the word Reload.Aiden exhaled in relief.Thankfully, the games mechanics hadnt changed since his rebirth.This meant it was time for the best part.Chapter 3 Aidens Secondary Hidden Class, the WealthmancerAidens heart raced as his hands trembled.He reached for the golden button on the screen and slammed on it.Please enter the amount you wish to top up.He didnt even hesitate before maxing it out entirely.Aiden kept his life savings in his bank account, including the two billion he made from selling his shares, plus another 50 million hed borrowed by mortgaging his luxury villa.Together with what hed saved before, he had a total of 2.2 billion.Each dollar equaled one mark, which meant he would receive 2.2 billion marks in the game.If anyone ever found out hed dumped that kind of money into a game, theyd probably call him insane.To Aiden, it was a deal straight from heaven.Three days from now, the value of these marks would skyrocket once Doomsday was officially launched and synced with reality.One mark would equal 10 dollars.Once the reload was successful, his 2.2 billion marks would be worth 22 billion dollars—ten times what hed started with.And even that number couldnt capture their real value.The reload system would only be available for ten minutes during the private beta launch.Nearly no one would think of topping up, and those who did would only spend small amounts.Upon the games official release, in-game currency would become scarce.Sure, players could still buy marks with cash, but it would be difficult to convert huge sums like ten billion.As time went on, players would realize just how critical marks were.They might sell off small amounts to cover real-life expenses, but no one would be dumb enough to sell everything.There would be demand without supply.Meanwhile, Aidens 2.2 billion marks would be his startup capital for the new world.As Aiden keyed in the figure, his pulse quickened.Realistically, a financial transfer this massive would have triggered multiple alerts from government regulators.No game would ever allow such a transaction to go through instantly.However, Doomsday wasnt just any ordinary game.Even so, he couldnt help but feel uneasy, wondering if itd work this time.Congratulations, your top-up is successful!Yeah!Moments later, Aiden clenched his fists in excitement as a line of astronomical numbers appeared on the screen.He remembered an old saying that money couldnt buy happiness, but it could make a persons entire week.Right now, Aiden was experiencing that high.With this kind of starting advantage, plus everything he remembered about Doomsday, he was confident that he could rise to the very top.Hed even crush those nepo babies who had every resource at their fingertips.Ding!Suddenly, a crisp mechanical chime sounded.Congratulations, Nighthale. You are the first player to reload your system, with a single recharge exceeding one billion marks. A rare hidden class reward has been unlocked.Ding!Hidden class detected. Updating the system…Ding!You have obtained a secondary class—the Wealthmancer. Your current classes include Beastmaster and the Wealthmancer.What? You can unlock hidden classes just by spending money? Aiden froze for a second, then burst out laughing in disbelief and delight.Beyond the typical classes players could start with or evolve into, rare hidden classes existed as well.These could only be unlocked by meeting very specific, mysterious conditions.There was an unspoken rule that hidden classes werent necessarily the strongest, but the strongest always came from a hidden class.Their attributes and talents were far beyond anything ordinary classes could offer.That was why even a rumor about a hidden class was enough to send the entire player base into a frenzy.Meanwhile, what Aiden received wasnt just a hidden class—it was a secondary class.This meant his original starting class hadnt been replaced at all.He was now both a Beastmaster and the Wealthmancer.Aiden quickly pulled up his Attributes Panel to check on his Wealthmancers stats.You are now viewing attributes for the Wealthmancer.Innate Talent: Fortune Flux (Level 1). As a Wealthmancer, you possess the ability to generate wealth. Your total marks increase by one percent each day.Innate Talent: Vaultbound (Level 1). A Wealthmancer never loses whats his. Upon death, you retain all marks and items.Innate Talent: Divine Prosperity (Level 1). Wealth attracts fortune. Permanently increases Luck by 50 points.Innate Talent: Absolute Aura (Level 1). Even the shabbiest man shines when hes generous. Permanently increases Charisma by 50 points.Innate Talent: Power of Wealth (Level 1). A Wealthmancer remains a divine being. For every one million marks you spend, gain one random attribute point. Maximum of 100 points per day.Gosh! Aiden froze in shock, his eyes widening.He knew a hidden class like the Wealthmancer would come in handy, but not this powerful!Any one of these talents alone could shake the entire game, but having all five?This shook Aiden to the core, even when he had already experienced the game in his past life.He rubbed his eyes again just to make sure he wasnt hallucinating.Forget the rest.For starters, Fortune Flux was already an amazing talent.With 2.2 billion in his possession, that talent meant an extra 22 million marks every single day without having to do anything!Paired with the Power of Wealth, Aiden could splurge on anything, only to have his attributes grow even stronger.Just spending for fun would earn him 22 attribute points per day, which was insane.The more I spend, the more powerful I become. Now thats awesome!Vaultbound was another useful talent.After all, death penalties were brutal beyond belief in Doomsday.If a player got killed, theyd lose 20 percent of all their attributes.Worse, every piece of gear, item, and mark they carried would drop on the spot.Because of that, most players never carried much and kept their marks in the NPC-run banks instead.But unlike actual banks, the ones in Doomsday did not pay interest.On the contrary, these banks charged players outrageous storage fees instead.The more one deposited, the higher the fee.For instance, if Aiden stored all his 2.2 billion marks in a bank, hed have to pay 22 million marks every three months just for safekeeping.Aiden would lose 88 million a year just to keep his money in a vault.To make things worse, there was always the risk of a bank owner disappearing with everyones savings.The rules were unfair, but players had to abide by them.For years, storing marks had been one of the biggest challenges in Doomsday.Now that Aiden had obtained Vaultbound, he didnt have to worry about that anymore.He could keep his marks with him, enjoy as Fortune Flux grew his wealth, and never lose anything if he died.A glint flashed across Aidens eyes as he smirked.Once I make a name for myself, I could open my own private bank. Ill charge a lower storage fee…Ill earn interest off my clients marks, and grow that with Fortune Flux. Its a guaranteed profit with no risk at all!Hed use other peoples money to make himself richer, and theyd even thank him for it afterward.Now that was what being a Wealthmancer was all about.

Chapter 1 A Second Chance at Life After Getting His Heart StolenAiden, do you think youre something special just because youre pretty well-off? Giving me all that money isnt actually helping!In fact, its an insult to my dignity!The searing pain in his chest hadnt faded yet, but his memories flooded back like a tide.Had he been reborn?Aiden Kroger stared blankly at the girl in front of him.Piper Langley seemed pretty and innocent, but she was full of pride and arrogance.Aiden had loved Piper for more than half his life, and she was the woman he loved the most.Well, he once did.He had been obsessed with her to the point of self-destruction, and it wasnt an exaggeration.Everyone at Kroger High knew Aiden was rich, loyal, and a hopeless romantic.Piper came from a poor family, so Aiden paid for her tuition.Hed give her whatever she wanted—be it food, clothes, or the most expensive things.She used to be a broke student who could barely afford to stay in school, yet under his care, she lived more comfortably than ninety-nine percent of people in the world.It all started with Doomsday, the virtual game.Those who grew stronger in the game gained extraordinary powers in real life.The worlds order collapsed, and society fell into chaos.Even in that hellish reality, Aiden did everything he could to protect Piper.At the start of the game, he spent a fortune to train her, afraid she might get hurt while leveling up.When she complained about her lousy equipment, he sold off all his familys assets just to buy her a divine weapon.Whenever he obtained a rare opportunity or valuable gear, Piper was always the first person he thought of.He poured his heart, effort, and every resource he had into Piper, turning her from a mere newbie into one of the top-ranked powerhouses of Dominion.Aiden believed his sincerity would be reciprocated, but on the night of their engagement, Piper cut open his chest and ripped out his heart with her bare hands.That memory was forever ingrained in his mind.Asking her why shed done that, Piper simply held his beating heart in her hands and sneered.Aiden, did you really think money could buy my love? Did you think giving me resources meant you could guilt-trip me emotionally? Youre wrong! I might have accepted your gifts, but that doesnt mean I accepted your feelings.She continued, Im worth way more than that. For the record, I achieved all that I have today through my own hard work. That rich-boy attitude of yours disgusts me, and youll never understand my pain. Martins the only one who does, but hes dying. Giving him your heart is the only useful thing youll ever do.Dont worry, though. Didnt you say you love me? Once I give your heart to Martin, Id still be able to hear it beating every day. How does that sound? Arent you touched by my final gift to you? she said.At that moment, Aiden felt nothing but emptiness.After all, his heart was gone.All those years of devotion had only been a one-sided illusion.He thought hed die a cold and painful death, but fate had other plans when the Heavens gave him a second chance.I gave up everything for you, Piper. I protected you with all my heart, he thought to himself.You had divine weapons and hidden classes—things that others could only dream of! In the end, you called it an insult to your dignity?This life, Ill take back every gift you took as charity and humiliation. Lets see if your so-called pride could ever match the achievements you had in your last life. And when the time comes, I will return blow for blow and make you die in the worst kind of pain!Aiden felt a coldness creep through him.He pressed his hand to his chest, feeling the phantom ache of having his heart ripped out.Aiden, are you deaf? Do you even hear me?On the street, Piper frowned at him.Seeing him stand there in a daze and refusing to let go of the bank card in his hand made her expression grim.Do you think I need your money? Ill have you know that Im only accepting your money to preserve your pride, got it?If you dont let go, dont ever come looking for me again!Aiden pulled himself out of his memory and glanced down at the card.He had planned on giving her 200,000 to spend this month.In the past, he wouldve panicked if Piper told him not to visit her anymore.Hed quickly explain himself, doing everything to make her accept the money.But now, he couldnt care less about anyones pride.Aidens expression remained cold as he withdrew the bank card.Youre right. Giving you money was my mistake, he uttered flatly.Finally! Its about time you understand, Piper muttered with a scoff.You have no idea how much pressure I feel whenever I take your money. Everyone calls me a gold digger who cant let you go, but they have no idea Im only doing it for your sake.Aiden almost laughed from anger, and he slipped the card into his pocket.Relax. From now on, Ill never give you another cent.Piper froze, her hand still hanging in the air.What was going on?In the past, whenever she said something like that, Aiden would have panicked and rushed to hand her the card with an apologetic smile.What kind of new trick was this?She figured he must be pulling some stunt to get her attention, but since she was short on cash right now, she didnt have the patience for his games.I didnt mean it like that, she said, softening her tone.Just take note next time, got it? Since youve come all this way, Ill do you a favor and take the card.She reached out her hand again, expecting him to obediently hand it over.Get lost.Aidens words hit like ice, and he turned on his heel before walking away.He couldnt believe how blind hed been before.Why was he obsessed with her?Had she cast a spell over him?Piper blinked, stunned.Shed never seen the usually spineless Aiden act like this.At once, her face twisted with anger.Aiden! Do you think this pathetic push-and-pull routine is going to get my attention?Im warning you! If you walk away now, dont ever come looking for me again!Ill never take anything from you again, even if you beg me to!Aiden stopped in his tracks.Piper smirked, thinking shed won again.She only needed to blackmail him, and hed come crawling back.But instead, Aiden turned around, his expression cold and distant.He pointed at her feet.I almost forgot that I bought those shoes on your feet. Since you said youll never take anything from me again, take them off now, he ordered.Aiden!Pipers expression froze, and her face twisted in fury.She trembled, her voice shaking with rage.Dont think youre something special just because youre rich! Do you think Id fall for this? Martins right—the rich will always look down on us! I see it now.She added, Also, once you give something away, its not yours anymore. You dont get to ask for it back!Whats wrong? Cant bear to part with them? Aiden sneered.You!Piper gritted her teeth, her expression dark.She yanked off the pair of designer shoes worth tens of thousands, then threw them at his feet.Her entire body trembled in anger.Remember this, Aiden! Even if you beg, Ill never speak to you again!Thank God for that.Aiden let out a snort, kicked the shoes into a nearby trash pile, and walked away.Behind him, Piper shrieked, Im giving you one last chance! If you beg right now, maybe Ill forgive you!Aiden? Aiden! Youll regret this! Youll definitely regret this!Aiden didnt even look back. To him, her words were nothing but background noise.He had no time to waste on a manipulative woman like her.After all, he had something far more important to do, which was to load up his account.Upon checking, Doomsdays private beta launch would kick off in a week.And for ten short minutes before it began, the games top-up system would be activated.Before then, he needed to gather as much money as possible.Chapter 2 Entering Doomsday With Two Billion in the BankBack home, Aiden dialed a number.Well, if it isnt the great romantic himself. Whats the matter? Did you finally remember that I exist?An irritatingly smug voice came from the other end.Aiden answered icily, Cut the crap, Carter. Youve always wanted my shares, havent you? Im selling them all for two billion. Do you want them or not?Youre selling your shares?Carter was immediately excited.Ill take them, of course! But theyre probably worth a billion at best. Asking for two is daylight robbery! he argued.Two billion, and not a penny less, Aiden said flatly.If youre not interested, Ill ask someone else.Hold up! Come on, lets talk this through, Carter said quickly, submitting to Aiden at once.Dont sell them to someone else. Ill give you two billion for your shares.Great. Youve got five days to complete the paperwork and wire the money to my account. Given your status, that shouldnt be a problem, right? Aiden said lazily.Carter hesitated.That wont be an issue, but with that much cash, Ill have to smooth things over with a few people. Therell be some losses and taxes…Thats your problem, Aiden answered, cutting him off at once.I want the money in five days. A penny less, and you wont be getting the shares.He hung up without another word, not the least bit worried the deal would fall through.After all, he knew no one wanted those shares more desperately than his cousin, Carter Kroger.Everyone at Kroger High knew that Aiden was a rich kid with family assets worth several hundred million.However, no one knew his real background ran far deeper than it seemed.His parents had founded Kroger Group, one of Grendolas largest corporations worth several billion.In truth, very few rich kids across the nation could compare to Aiden.Unfortunately, a tragic accident had taken both his parents lives ten years ago.The massive conglomerate couldnt possibly be held together by an eight-year-old boy, and soon, greedy relatives and so-called family friends claimed the Kroger Group bit by bit.All that was left to him was a small portion of the companys shares and assets that his parents had set aside for him beforehand, and it was worth just over a billion.Even so, that amount wouldve been more than enough for Aiden to lead a comfortable life.Too bad hed fallen for Piper in his previous life.Perhaps it was that emptiness and the lack of family love that made him pour so much of himself into her, as if she could fill that void.Even after she hurt him again and again, he never once stopped giving.If his parents had still been alive, and if hed grown up in a complete, loving home, Aiden would not have foolishly thrown everything away for someone like her.Guess thats all in the past.Aiden pressed a hand to his chest, his gaze firming with resolve.It was his desperate longing for love that had ruined him in his previous life.This time, he wouldnt make the same mistake.He would ascend the throne alone.At the same time, hed do everything to uncover the truth behind his parents so-called accident back then.Right now, the Kroger Group was in the middle of an intense power struggle.Whoever got hold of Aidens shares would gain the biggest authority in the company.Despite Carter paying twice the market value for his shares, Aiden was certain that his cousin wouldnt hesitate to purchase his shares for two billion.If it werent for the fact that he needed the money within five days, Aiden could have asked for more.Honestly, it was a bit of a loss.But compared to the massive advantage that two billion would bring him in the early stages of Doomsday, that loss meant nothing.With the experience of his previous life, Aiden was confident he could multiply that money several thousand times its original value.Just as he expected, Carter rushed over within five days.Hed brought all the paperwork, eager to finalize the deal.Once Aiden confirmed the funds had arrived in his account, he calmly signed one document after another.I dont know why you changed your mind all of a sudden, but this is probably the smartest decision youve ever made, Carter said with a broad smile.With the transfer complete, Carter was on cloud nine.From now on, his faction would hold absolute control over the Kroger Group.Just live your life as a rich but pitiful man, and stop chasing those unrealistic dreams, he said smugly.The Kroger Group may have belonged to your parents once, but thats ancient history.From now on, the company has nothing to do with you.
